This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
9:59 AM Defendant Nathan James Tuttle in court, in custody.  Attorney Mark Adam Fruehauf in court for State of Wisconsin. Court calls case. Defendant wishes to proceed without counsel. Court informs of right to counsel. Defendant does not wish to reschedule, wants to proceed today. Defendant makes statements. Court questions defendant regarding ability to proceed. Concerned about ability to represent himself. State is also concerned regarding competency. Recommends competency be raised and proceed under 971.14.
Court addresses defendant regarding concerns. Court suggests matter be stayed. Finds good cause for adjournment. 
Court addresses Attorney Ryan Reid who appears via zoom for another matter. Attorney Reid will appoint a public defender in this matter.
Status conference scheduled for November 7, 2022 at 09:30 am.

ADDRESS INFO for Nathan James Tuttle
Current: 1009 Baxter Ave, Superior, WI 54880 United States  (Effective: 10-26-2022)
Prior: 9469 Tyler St, Blaine, MN 55434

1:27 PM Defendant Nathan James Tuttle appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Ryan Reid appears for Defendant. Attorney Peter Kruger in court for State of Wisconsin. Court calls case. Address verified as 1009 Baxter Avenue. Acknowledges receipt, waives reading, pleads not guilty, request prelim. Court accepts pleas.
State requests $500 cash, no contact with Alexis Steltz. No criminal priors. 
Attorney Reid indicates has Superior address. Family lives here. Agrees with no record. Asks for signature bond or lower cash bond. 
Court makes statements. Court orders $250 cash, 1000 signature bond, with conditions of no contact with Alexis Steltz
Preliminary hearing and Arraignment scheduled for November 2, 2022 at 10:00 am.
